--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Uppsala Atomistic Spin Dynamics (UppASD) project was initially conceived and
developed at the Division of Materials Theory at Uppsala University. The UppASD
project has been funded by a grant from the European Research Council (ERC), the
Swedish Research Council, the Knut and Alice Wallenberg Foundation and eSSENCE.

The team behind this effort are (listed alphabetically)

Anders Bergman, Uppsala University <anders.bergman@physics.uu.se>
Lars Bergqvist, KTH Royal Institute of Technology (email <lbergqv@kth.se>)
Jonathan Chico, Forschungzentrum Julich (email <j.chico@fz-juelich.de>)
Anna Delin, KTH Royal Institute of Technology
Olle Eriksson, Uppsala University
Johan Hellsvik, KTH Royal Institute of Technology (email <hellsvik@kth.se>)
Johan Mentink, Raadboud University
Lars Nordström, Uppsala University
Manuel Pereiro, Uppsala University
Björn Skubic, formerly Uppsala University (now at Ericsson Research)

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The UppASD code also includes additional routines from other 
authors/software
- Profiling routines from BigDFT (http://bigdft.org)
- Mersenne-Twister RNG (http://www.math.keio.ac.jp/matumoto/emt.htm)
- Ziggurat RNG (http://people.sc.fsu.edu/~jburkardt/f_src/ziggurat/ziggurat.html)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
